Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Core and slice the @apple{1}(cored and sliced into 12 wedges) into 12 wedges (no need to peel). Peel the @garlic cloves{2} and grate half of the cloves (or use a #garlic press{}), leaving the other half as whole cloves.

When boiling, add the potatoes and whole garlic cloves to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @green beans{150%grams}. Pop them onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and season.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @THIS™ Isn't Pork Sausages{6%units}, turning occasionally, until golden, ~{7-8%minutes}. Set aside for now.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Wipe out the pan and pop back on medium heat. Melt in the @butter{20%grams}. Once melted, add the sliced apple and fry stirring occasionally, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in the remaining grated garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir through the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, @wholegrain mustard{17%grams} and @water{75%milliliters}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Simmer until thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, once the potatoes and garlic are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{splash} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season and cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the apple sauce has thickened, stir through the @creme fraiche{75%grams} and @mixed herbs{1%sachet}.

Return the THIS™ Isn't Pork Sausages to the sauce and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn to coat evenly.

When everything's ready, share the garlic mash between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the THIS™ Isn't Pork Sausages and spoon over the creamy apple sauce.

Serve the green beans alongside.

Enjoy!